    "summary": "The fundamental difference between ballpoint and gel pens lies in their ink formulation: ballpoint pens use highly viscous, oil-based paste ink that dries quickly but requires more pressure, while gel pens use low-viscosity, water-based gel ink that provides a smoother, more vibrant writing experience but takes longer to dry and may smudge. The choice dictates the required writing pressure and the resulting color vibrancy and drying speed.",
