    "summary": "Feathers (quills) established the fundamental mechanism for controlled ink flow in writing instruments. The hollow shaft served as an ink reservoir, while a critical slit in the tip utilized capillary action to regulate steady ink delivery. Modern pen inventors replicated this successful reservoir and capillary system using durable materials like metal, leading directly to the fountain pen design.",
